
[1]quietly

   QUI'ETLY, adv.

   1. In a quiet state; without motion; in a state of rest; as, to lie or
   sit quietly.

   2. Without tumult, alarm, dispute or disturbance; peaceably; as, to
   live quietly.

   3. Calmly; without agitation or violent emotion; patiently. submit
   quietly to unavoidable evils.
